rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an organization to information about the organization's registration. Registration includes the registering organization or agency, the dates and status of registration, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registered with

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.organization to its associated mso:religion.religion. Note that this is a broader property than religion.religious_organization.associated_with, since it allows an organization that is not necessarily a religious organization to be associated with a religion. For example, a political party may be associated with a particular religion, or a company may specialize in halal or kosher products.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Religion

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.organization to information about the area(s) in which the organization operates. For global organizations, the scope is "international".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Geographic Scope

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.organization to its mso:organization.sector(s) of operation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sector

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.organization to its slogan.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Slogan

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:organization.organization to the mso:organization.spin_off entities that collect the data on spin-offs from this organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spin Offs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.organization to the mso:organization.spin_off entities collecting data in the spin-offs from which this organization came.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Spun off from

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an organization to a webpage providing a listing of the staff of the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Staff Page

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The unique number identifying a business or other organization for tax purposes. Also known as a TIN, Employer Identification Number or EIN.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tax Identification Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an organization to a standard descriptor for he kind of organization that it is, such as Professional Association, NGO or Fraternal Organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship relating an organization to another that in some manner represents its "predecessor". The new organization may have been created as a rename, an acquisition, or a merger. This relationship is a linear one, and the predecessor company ceases to exist when the succeeding company is created. Whenever possible, use the more specific properties of merger, acquisition, and renaming to create the relation. Compare this to organization.relationship, which is a co-temporal relationship that exists between two companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Predecessor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a predecessor organization relationship to the organization that resulted from the rename, merger, or acquisition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a predecessor organization relationship to the percentage share of the preceeding organization that the the resulting organization obtained.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Percentage Share

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a predecessor organization relationship to the organization that is considered the preceding organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Predecessor

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on a partnership between two organizations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Partnership
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This type is not necessary. The property mso:organization.organization.partnerships can be used to relate two affiliated organizations. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:organization.organization.partnerships]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying the organizations that form the given partnership.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Member
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: This property is not necessary. The property mso:organization.organization.partnerships can be used to relate two affiliated organizations. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:organization.organization.partnerships]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about an organization's rank in a given source.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ranking
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use the more general type mso:award.ranking instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:award.ranking]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an organization's ranking relationship to the date the ranking was in effect.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a ranking relationship to the organization holding the rank.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an organization's ranking relationship to the rank the company occupies in the ranking.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an organization's ranking relationship to the source of the ranking. For example, "Forbes" would be the source of the ranked list "Forbes' top 100 Places to Work".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Source

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization that collects used items, e.g. cans, bottles, plastic bags, etc., and, in some cases, processes them into new materials or products to prevent waste of resources.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recycling Center

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship type collecting facts about an organization's registration. Facts in this type include the registering agency, registration id, date of registration, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Registration

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.registration to an mso:organization.organization with which the registered_organization is affiliated. Affiliation is the organizational grouping in the context of the IRS group ruling.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Affiliation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a registration relationship to a non-profit designation. This is the broadest classification for a non-profit. For example, the American Cancer Society has a broad classification of "Educational Organization" with a subdesignation of '501(c)(3)'. See also mso:organization.registration.non_profit_subdesignation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Non-profit Designation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.registration to the sub-designations the organization has under the registering agency. This property captures fine-grained distinctions in registration. Please use mso:organization.registration.non_profit_designation for the broadest designations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Subdesignation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the registered address of the organization with the given agency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registered Address

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a registration relationship to the organization that is registered.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a registration relationship to the agency that has registered or certified the organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registering Agency

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a registration relationship to the id or number assigned to the organization by the agency.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Regisration ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a registration relationship to the registration status, e.g. registered, revoked or in process, that the organization has.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Registration Status

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type expressing the relationship between an organization and its sub-organizations. A subsidiary is a company completely or partially owned and completely or partially controlled by another company, called the parent company. See also mso:business.division and mso:organization.organization_predecessor_relationship, the latter of which expresses a linear predecessor/successor relationship between companies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Relationship

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the child organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Child

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a subsidiary relationship to the date the relationship ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the parent organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a subsidiary relationship to the percentage share the parent company owns of the subsidiary.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Percentage Share

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all research organization. These are organizations whose primary directive is some branch of research. This includes medical research, historical research, and so forth.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Research Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.research_organization to the mso:media_common.subject that is the topic of the organization's research.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Research Subject

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type representing the collection of all organization roles. These are the functions a person plays within an organization.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Role

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a role to information about leaders of an organization that have the role.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Governors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a role to information about leaders of an organization that have the role.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Leaders

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the extent of an organization's reach, e.g. "international".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Scope

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an organization scope to an organization that has this scope.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organizations with this Scope

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for the subject focus of an organization, e.g. immunization or economic development.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Sector

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an organization sector to an organization in this sector.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organizations in this Sector

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization that provides services to senior citizens in the community.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Senior Citizen Assistance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data on a spin-off of one organization from another.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Spin-off

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:organization.spin_off entity to the child organization that is spun off from the parent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Child Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.spin_off to the date the spin-off occurred.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use time.event.end_date or time.event.start_date instead. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:time.event.start_date]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:organization.spin_off to the parent mso:organization.organization from which the child organization was created.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Parent Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization whose focus is dedicated to business and/or trade. Includes labor unions, manufacturing agents, manufacturing representatives, business associations, and trade associations.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Trade Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for groupings of organizations by common characteristics, e.g. business model or legal structure.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Organization Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization made up of military veterans whose mission is to assist veterans and their families.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Veterans Organization

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An organization that provides services to minors in the community.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Youth Assistance
